Package: postgrustsql
Architecture: amd64
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}, adduser
Suggests: postgresql-client
Description: PostgreSQL-compatible database server written in Rust
 PostgrustSQL is a PostgreSQL-compatible database server implementation
 written in Rust, featuring:
  * PostgreSQL wire protocol compatibility
  * 23 data types (~45% PostgreSQL compatibility)
  * MVCC (Multi-Version Concurrency Control)
  * Transaction support (BEGIN/COMMIT/ROLLBACK)
  * FOREIGN KEY constraints and JOINs
  * B-tree and Hash indexes
  * Binary storage with WAL (Write-Ahead Log)
  * Page-based storage for efficient writes
  * VACUUM command for MVCC cleanup
  * Extended WHERE operators (BETWEEN, LIKE, IN, IS NULL)
  * CASE expressions and set operations (UNION/INTERSECT/EXCEPT)
  .
 This package includes:
  * postgrustql - database server
  * pgr_cli - interactive CLI client
  * pgr_dump - backup utility
  * pgr_restore - restore utility
